                                <ns0:support>
                                    <ns0:p>Large slab of grey/brown stone. Forms a pair with <ns0:ref target="http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001160">ISic001160</ns0:ref>, as they are similar in size, material, and the form and shape of the letters. All sides are almost square, but for the broken top left corner. The back is almost flat, but there is a slight taper on the sides towards the back</ns0:p>
